	"title": "Ma journée — Daily routine",
	"objective": "Describe a typical day and how often you do things (A1: can describe daily routines and habits simply).",
	"bridge": {
		"title": "Bridge from Hindi / English: present tense + frequency words",
		"body": "French has no separate “habitual present” — the simple present covers habits: *Je travaille le matin* = “I work in the morning.” Add frequency words like **souvent** (often), **toujours** (always), **tous les jours** (every day). Place them after the verb: *Je bois souvent du chai.* This matches Hindi रोज़ / अक्सर placement closely."
